#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an10.39"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an10.39:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 10 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 10 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an10.39:0.2"
msgid "4. Upālivagga "
msgstr "4. With Upāli "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an10.39:0.3"
msgid "39. Paṭhamaānandasutta "
msgstr "39. With Ānanda (1st) "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.75, sc1
msgctxt "an10.39:1.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā ānando yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then Venerable Ānanda went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to the Buddha: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an10.39:1.2"
msgid "“‘saṅghabhedo saṅghabhedo’ti, bhante, vuccati. "
msgstr "“Sir, they speak of ‘schism in the Saṅgha’. "

msgctxt "an10.39:1.3"
msgid "Kittāvatā nu kho, bhante, saṅgho bhinno hotī”ti? "
msgstr "How is schism in the Saṅgha defined?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an10.39:1.4"
msgid "“Idhānanda, bhikkhū adhammaṃ dhammoti dīpenti, dhammaṃ adhammoti dīpenti, avinayaṃ vinayoti dīpenti … pe … "
msgstr "“Ānanda, it’s when a mendicant explains what is not the teaching as the teaching … "

msgctxt "an10.39:1.5"
msgid "paññattaṃ tathāgatena apaññattaṃ tathāgatenāti dīpenti. "
msgstr "and what was prescribed by the Realized One as not prescribed by the Realized One. "

msgctxt "an10.39:1.6"
msgid "Te imehi dasahi vatthūhi avakassanti apakassanti āveni kammāni karonti āveni pātimokkhaṃ uddisanti. "
msgstr "On these ten grounds they split off and go their own way. They perform legal acts autonomously and recite the monastic code autonomously. "

msgctxt "an10.39:1.7"
msgid "Ettāvatā kho, ānanda, saṅgho bhinno hotī”ti. "
msgstr "That is how schism in the Saṅgha is defined.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an10.39:2.1"
msgid "“Samaggaṃ pana, bhante, saṅghaṃ bhinditvā kiṃ so pasavatī”ti? "
msgstr "“But sir, what does someone who has caused a schism in a harmonious Saṅgha bring upon themselves?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an10.39:2.2"
msgid "“Kappaṭṭhikaṃ, ānanda, kibbisaṃ pasavatī”ti. "
msgstr "“They bring upon themselves evil that lasts for an eon.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an10.39:2.3"
msgid "“Kiṃ pana, bhante, kappaṭṭhikaṃ kibbisan”ti? "
msgstr "“But sir, what is the evil that lasts for an eon?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an10.39:2.4"
msgid "“Kappaṃ, ānanda, nirayamhi paccatīti—"
msgstr "“They burn in hell for an eon, Ānanda. "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.76, sc3
msgctxt "an10.39:3.1"
msgid "Āpāyiko nerayiko, "
msgstr "A schismatic remains for the eon "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an10.39:3.2"
msgid "Kappaṭṭho saṃghabhedako; "
msgstr "in a place of loss, in hell. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an10.39:3.3"
msgid "Vaggarato adhammaṭṭho, "
msgstr "Basing themselves in what is not the teaching, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an10.39:3.4"
msgid "Yogakkhemā padhaṃsati; "
msgstr "favoring factions, they destroy their sanctuary. "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: bhinditvā → bhetvāna (bj, s1-3, pts1) | bhitvāna (mr)
msgctxt "an10.39:3.5"
msgid "Saṃghaṃ samaggaṃ bhinditvā, "
msgstr "After causing schism in a harmonious Saṅgha, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an10.39:3.6"
msgid "Kappaṃ nirayamhi paccatī”ti. "
msgstr "they burn in hell for an eon.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an10.39:3.7"
msgid "Navamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

